	<title>The user should be notified of a corrupt prefs.js file (some prefs were lost)</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">When prefs.js is corrupt we copy it to Invalidprefs.js to give the user
a chance to rescue the lost settings manually.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">We need to notify the user that there was a problem, something like:
  "Some of your preferences has been lost due to a corrupt file.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">See &lt;URL&gt; for further instructions."</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
